    <p>One practitioner on Reddit described the early freelance experience: <em>"After a couple of months, I made my first sale of $39. Over time that grew to cover my bills."</em> That pattern &mdash; a long dry period followed by compounding momentum &mdash; is representative of content and commission-based methods. It is the main reason <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/affiliate-marketing-statistics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">95% of aspiring affiliates quit</a> before income materialises.</p>
